@startuml
title Assets and Drawing - Beginner View

skinparam classAttributeIconSize 0

class Image {
	+ loadFromFile(path)
}

class SpriteSheet {
	+ sprite(coord)
}

class Font {
	+ atlas(size)
	+ computeStringSize(text, size)
}

class Mesh {
	+ addShape(...)
}

class RenderCommand
class "ImageRenderCommand" as ImageCommand
class "SpriteRenderCommand" as SpriteCommand
class "TextRenderCommand" as TextCommand
class "Draw*MeshRenderCommand" as MeshCommand

Image <|-- SpriteSheet
RenderCommand <|-- ImageCommand
RenderCommand <|-- SpriteCommand
RenderCommand <|-- TextCommand
RenderCommand <|-- MeshCommand
ImageCommand --> Image
SpriteCommand --> SpriteSheet
TextCommand --> Font
MeshCommand --> Mesh

note bottom
Assets hold data such as pixels, sprites, glyphs,
or vertices. Render commands describe how those
assets should be drawn during a frame.
end note

@enduml
